						<summary>

						<p>Kshaya, Chittirai 25 = c. 14th-15th Century.</p>						

						<p>The temple trustees of Aḻimbil-nayiṉār and the ten <hi rend="italic">perumpar</hi> (mentioned in the above inscription) decided to contribute a sum of 45 <hi rend="italic">poṉ</hi> annually to the temple for offerings and repairs. The money is to be collected from the temple trustees, from the tolls and fairs and from the <hi rend="italic">Sūdra</hi> members among the temple trustees.</p>						

						</summary>
